verses.verse: Unto you lift I up <WH5375> my eyes <WH5869>, O you that dwell <WH3427> in the heavens <WH8064>.

Behold <WH5869>, as the eyes of servants <WH5650> look unto the hand <WH3027> of their masters <WH113>, and as the eyes <WH5869> of a maiden <WH8198> unto the hand <WH3027> of her mistress <WH1404>; so our eyes <WH5869> wait upon the Lord <WH3068> our God <WH430>, until that he have mercy upon us <WH2603>.
Have mercy <WH2603> upon us <WH3068>, O Lord, have mercy <WH2603> upon us <WH7227>: for we are exceedingly filled <WH7646> with contempt <WH937>.
Our soul <WH5315> is exceedingly <WH7227> filled <WH7646> with the scorning <WH3933> of those that are at ease <WH7600>, and with the contempt <WH937> of the proud <WH1343>.
